Web APIs are how much of the modern web speaks - services speaking HTTP and JSON are ubiquitous, and nearly everything from your phone to your TV interacts with one of them. We'll go over how APIs are structured and versioned, why you should validate your data, and why you should have them in the first place -- and what other best practices are when creating them.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">HawkOwl</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 11 Aug 2014 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/3104/building-better-web-apis-by-hawkowl</guid><enclosure url="http://mirror.linux.org.au/pub/pycon-au/pyconau2014/67-out.ogv" length="None" type="video/ogg"></enclosure><media:group><media:content url="http://mirror.linux.org.au/pub/pycon-au/pyconau2014/67-out.ogv" mime_type="video/ogg"></media:content><media:content url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pXa4SV3E5JY" mime_type="video/flv"></media:content></media:group><media:thumbnail url="http://i.ytimg.com/vi/pXa4SV3E5JY/hqdefault.jpg"></media:thumbnail></item></channel></rss>